JOHANNESBURG ANC Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says the ANC will continue to lose power if claims of state capture are left unchecked.He says the ANC should support the call for a commission of inquiry into allegations of state capture.He says the party will continue losing support if these claims are left unchecked.WATCH: We are facing a state capture coup: Jonas at Hani memorialRamaphosa was speaking at a Chris Hani memorial lecture in Uitenhage in the Eastern Cape. The ANC therefore must, should support the establishment of an effective, credible mechanism to investigate these claims," said Ramaphosa."I support that there be a judicial commission of inquiry...It is the truth that will unite our movement once again."We cannot leave this matter unattended. It is causing problems within our ranks. eNCA